Seems like my birthdays been getting worse and worse each year. But I’m just happy for more life, and more blessings 🩵

Last week I had the most devastating birthday that I never imagined. I had the worst injury ever in my life.. As I was screaming on the floor through the excruciating pain, the only thought that was going through my head was, “this can’t be.. no please don’t let it be..” I thought that this was over for me. That hooping will never be the same. I have dealt with so many injuries within the last few years, from torn hamstring, torn rotator cuff, fractured ankle, fractured hand and many more.. But this time, it’s the most devastating and heartbreaking one of all. But I’ve been here before, this ain’t new to me. As hard as I fall, I’m just going to work harder to get back up. I’ve always said, every setback leads to a comeback, where the comeback is always stronger than the setback.

Never would I imagined seeing myself on a billboard outside Lakers Crypto.com Arena. Very blessed and grateful for the journey. Wouldn’t be here without all the love and support from all y’all 🙏🏽 Thank you @nike @nikebasketball @kobebryant 💜💛 #OnlyBasketball
